  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 9 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 1 critical, 17 high, 8 medium, 13 normal. Key bases needing attention include Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR), Chişinău (RMO/LUKK) and Katowice Wojciech Korfanty (KTW/EPKT); plus 15 other bases. 8 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is mist, thunderstorm / convective risk and fog / freezing fog  — most notably around Vilnius (VNO/EYVI), M. R. Štefánik (BTS/LZIB) and Poznań-Ławica (POZ/EPPO). Network hotspots: Lennart Meri Tallinn (TLL/EETN), Bergen Airport, Flesland (BGO/ENBR), Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM), Sandefjord Airport, Torp (TRF/ENTO), Olsztyn-Mazury (SZY/EPSY) and 4 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, snow / blowing snow and cold‑temperature performance penalties. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 5 airports changed status, led by Palanga (PLQ/EYPA), Priština Adem Jashari (PRN/BKPR), Ohrid St. Paul the Apostle (OHD/LWOH) and 2 others.",
